  "tutorial": "## Jira Data Center/Server Setup\n\n### Getting Your Jira URL\n\nYour Jira URL is your self-hosted Jira instance address (e.g., `https://jira.yourcompany.com`).\n\nThis server also supports Jira Cloud with API tokens.\n\n### Creating an API Token (Jira Cloud)\n\n1. Go to [id.atlassian.com/manage-profile/security/api-tokens](https://id.atlassian.com/manage-profile/security/api-tokens)\n2. Click **Create API token**\n3. Enter a label (e.g., \"MCP Server\")\n4. Click **Create** and copy the token\n\n### Personal Access Token (Jira Data Center)\n\nFor Jira Data Center 8.14+:\n1. Go to your profile settings\n2. Click **Personal Access Tokens**\n3. Create a new token\n\n### Required Information\n\n- **Jira URL**: Your Jira instance URL\n- **Email**: Your Jira account email (for Cloud)\n- **API Token**: The token you created above\n\n### Permissions\n\nThe API token inherits your account permissions. Ensure your account has access to the projects you want to manage.",
